{
  "stem": "4967.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm telling this because I come to the point later on I'd been in one of those.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But people got very weak.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't buy medication, not even a bandage, not even a dentist.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you  had trouble with a tooth, take an ordinary plier and pull it out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To go to the hospital, we knew it was dangerous, that they blow up the small ghetto hospital with the doctors, with the nurses, with the sisters, with the children.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was unbearable, too terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I saw it with my eyes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I couldn't believe in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And two days later, when it was settled and took stock of ourselves, we realized what had happened.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, by the way, I had my Bar Mitzvah in the camp, in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We wore ordinary clothing, not like in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Clothing was expensive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some people came from outskirts of Kovno, came with nothing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was the Jewish people who helped the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I, actually, when I moved into the ghetto the first time, and they made the ghetto smaller, I was accommodated to sleep in the synagogue, in Slobodka synagogue.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And still very religious Jewish people with beards, although they had to shave their beards, otherwise the Germans pulled them by their beards, cut off with scissors, give them a hiding, murder them, kick them, but religious life went on.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There used to be minyonem every morning, 4 o'clock in the morning, to daven.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], and whatever it is [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had a great uncle named Irs Miller.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He used to teach me my [NON-ENGLISH] for my Bar Mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
